obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (19196)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19196&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Banking ^1[Regulation]`
  line `Act, 1949.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^3***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^4`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "Companies" (w.e.f. 1-3-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1950, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 18-3-1950).`
  line
  line `3. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `4. 16th March, 1949, see Notification No. F. 4 (46)-FI/49, dated the 10th March, 1949, Gazette of India, 1949, Part I.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (19197)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 95 of 1956, s. 14 and the Schedule, for "Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)" (w.e.f. 14-1-1957).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19197&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not, save as hereinafter expressly provided, in derogation of the ^1[Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)],`
  line `any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (19198)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act not to apply to certain co-operative societies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 39 of 2020, s. 2, for section 3 (w.e.f. 26-6-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19198&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Act not to apply to certain co-operative societies.--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981 (61 of 1981), this Act shall not`
  line `apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a primary agricultural credit society; or`
  line
  line `(b) a co-operative society whose primary object and principal business is providing of longterm finance for agricultural development,`
  line
  line `if such society does not use as part of its name, or in connection with its business, the words "bank",`
  line `"banker" or "banking" and does not act as drawee of cheques.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (19199)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to suspend operation of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Dominion Legislature".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19199&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, if on a representation made`
  line `by the Reserve Bank in this behalf is satisfied that it is expedient so to do, may by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, suspend for such period, not exceeding sixty days, as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act, either generally or in relation to`
  line `any specified banking company.`
  line
  line `(2) In a case of special emergency, the Governor of the Reserve Bank, or in his absence a Deputy`
  line `Governor of the Reserve Bank nominated by him in this behalf may, by order in writing, exercise the`
  line `powers of the Central Government under sub-section (1) so however that the period of suspension shall`
  line `not exceed thirty days, and where the Governor or the Deputy Governor, as the case may be, does so, he`
  line `shall report the matter to the Central Government forthwith, and the order shall, as soon as may be, be`
  line `published in the Gazette of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, extend from time to time`
  line `the period of any suspension ordered under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) for such period, not`
  line `exceeding sixty days at any one time, as it thinks fit so however that the total period does not exceed`
  line `one year.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of any notification issued under sub-section (3) shall be laid on the table`
  line `of ^1[Parliament] as soon as may be after it is issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (19200)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19200&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[In this Act], unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) approved securities means the securities issued by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government or such other securities as may be specified by the Reserve Bank from time to time.]`
  line
  line `(b) banking means the accepting, for the purpose of lending or investment, of deposits of`
  line `money from the public, repayable on demand or otherwise, and withdrawable by cheque, draft,`
  line `order or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(c) banking company means any company which transacts the business of banking`
  line `^3[in India];`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any company which is engaged in the manufacture of goods or carries on any`
  line `trade and which accepts deposits of money from the public merely for the purpose of financing its`
  line `business as such manufacturer or trader shall not be deemed to transact the business of banking`
  line `within the meaning of this clause;`
  line
  line `^4[(ca) banking policy means any policy which is specified from time to time by the Reserve`
  line `Bank in the interest of the banking system or in the interest of monetary stability or sound economic`
  line `growth, having due regard to the interests of the depositors, the volume of deposits and other`
  line `resources of the bank and the need for equitable allocation and the efficient use of these deposits`
  line `and resources;]`
  line
  line `^5[(cc) branch or branch office, in relation to a banking company, means any branch or`
  line `branch office, whether called a pay office or sub-pay office or by any other name, at which deposits`
  line `are received, cheques cashed or moneys lent, and for the purposes of section 35 includes any place`
  line `of business where any other form of business referred to in sub-section (1) of section 6 is`
  line transacted;]
  line
  line `^6[(d) company means any company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956); and includes foreign company within the meaning of section 591 of that Act;]`
  line
  line `^7[(da) corresponding new bank means a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or`
  line `under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980`
  line `(40 of 1980);]`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) demand liabilities means liabilities which must be met on demand, and time liabilities`
  line `means liabilities which are not demand liabilities;`
  line
  line `^9[(ff) Deposit Insurance Corporation means the Deposit Insurance Corporation established`
  line `under section 3 of the Deposit Insurance Corporation Act, 1961 (47 of 1961);]`
  line
  line ^10-[
  line `^11* * * * *`
  line
  line `(ffb) Exim Bank means the Export-Import Bank of India established under section 3 of the`
  line `Export-Import Bank of India Act, 1981 (28 of 1981);]`
  line
  line `^12[(ffc) Reconstruction Bank means the Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India established`
  line `under Section 3 of the Industrial Reconstruction Bank of India Act, 1984 (62 of 1984);]`
  line
  line `^13[(ffd) National Housing Bank means the National Housing Bank established under section 3`
  line `of the National Housing Bank Act, 1987 (53 of 1987);]`
  line
  line `(g) gold includes gold in the form of coin, whether legal tender or not, or in the form of`
  line `bullion or ingot, whether refined or not;`
  line
  line `^14[(gg) managing agent includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) secretaries and treasurers,`
  line
  line `(ii) where the managing agent is a company, any director of such company, and any`
  line `member thereof who holds substantial interest in such company,`
  line
  line `(iii) where the managing agent is a firm, any partner of such firm;]`
  line
  line `^15[(h) managing director, in relation to a banking company, means a director who, by virtue of`
  line `of an agreement with the banking company or of a resolution passed by the banking company in`
  line `general meeting or by its Board of directors or, by virtue of its memorandum or articles of`
  line `association, is entrusted with the management of the whole, or substantially the whole of the affairs`
  line `of the company, and includes a director occupying the position of a managing director, by whatever`
  line `name called:]`
  line
  line `^16[Provided that the managing director shall exercise his powers subject to the superintendence,`
  line `control and direction of the Board of directors.]`
  line
  line `^17[(ha) National Bank means the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development`
  line `established under section 3 of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981`
  line `(61 of 1981);]`
  line
  line `^18[(hb) National Bank for financing Infrastructure and Development means the Institution`
  line `established under section 3 of the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development Act,`
  line 2021;
  line
  line `(hc) other development financial institution means a development financial institution`
  line `licensed under section 29 of the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development Act,`
  line 2021;]
  line
  line `^19* * * * *`
  line
  line `(j) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^17[(ja) regional rural bank means a regional rural bank established under section 3 of the`
  line `Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976);]`
  line
  line `^20* * * * *`
  line
  line `^21[(l) Reserve Bank means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934):]`
  line
  line `^20* * * * *`
  line
  line `(n) secured loan or advance means a loan or advance made on the security of assets the`
  line `market value of which is not at any time less than the amount of such loan or advance; and`
  line `unsecured loan or advance means a loan or advance not so secured;`
  line
  line `^22[(ni) Small Industries Bank means the Small Industries Development Bank of India`
  line `established under section 3 of the Small Industries Development Bank of India Act, 1989`
  line `(39 of 1989);]`
  line
  line `^23[(na) small-scale industrial concern mean an industrial concern in which the investment in`
  line `plant and machinery is not in excess of seven and a half lakhs of rupees or such higher amount, not`
  line `exceeding twenty lakhs of rupees, as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify in this behalf, having regard to the trends in industrial development and other`
  line `relevant factors;`
  line
  line `^24[(nb) Sponsor Bank has the meaning assigned to it in the Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976`
  line `(21 of 1976) :`
  line
  line `(nc) State Bank of India means the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955);]`
  line
  line `^25[(nd)] subsidiary bank has the meaning assigned to it in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary`
  line `Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `^26[(ne)] substantial interest,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to a company, means the holding of a beneficial interest by an individual or`
  line `his spouse or minor child, whether singly or taken together in the shares thereof, the amount`
  line `paid-up on which exceeds five lakhs of rupees or ten per cent. of the paid-up capital of the`
  line `company, whichever is less;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a firm, means the beneficial interest held therein by an individual or his`
  line `spouse or minor child, whether singly or taken together, which represents more than ten`
  line `per cent. of the total capital subscribed by all the partners of the said firm;]`
  line
  line `^27[(o) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.]`
  line
  line `^28* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1963, s. 6, for (1) In this Act (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18-1-2013).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 20 of 1950, s. 3, for in any State.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (e) omitted by Act 52 of 1953, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-12-1953).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 47 of 1961, s. 51 and the Second Schedule, Part II (w.e.f. 1-1-1962).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `11. Omitted by Act 53 of 2003, s. 12 and Schedule, Part II (w.e.f. 2-7-2004).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 62 of 1984, s. 71 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 20-3-1985).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 53 of 1987, s. 56 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 9-7-1988).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 2, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `16. Added by Act 58 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 1-5-1982).`
  line
  line `18 Ins. by Act 17 of 2021, s. 48 and the third Schedule (w.e.f. 19-4-2021).`
  line
  line `19. Omitted by Act 33 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `20. Omitted by Act 33 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `21. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 13, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `22. Ins. by Act 39 of 1989, s. 53 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 25-10-1989).`
  line
  line `23. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `24. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 13, (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `25. Clause (nb) re-lettered as clause (nd) by Act 1 of 1984, s. 13 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `26. Clause (nc) re-lettered as clause (ne) by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `27. Ins. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `28. Omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (19201)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Act to override memorandum, articles, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19201&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Act to override memorandum, articles, etc.--Save as otherwise expressly provided in this`
  line Act,--
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in the memorandum or articles of a banking company, or in any agreement executed by`
  line `it, or in any resolution passed by the banking company in general meeting or by its Board of Directors, whether the same be registered, executed or passed, as the case may be, before or after`
  line `the commencement of the Banking Companies (Amendment) Act, 1959 (33 of 1959); and`
  line
  line `(b) any provision contained in the memorandum, articles, agreement or resolution aforesaid`
  line `shall, to the extent to which it is repugnant to the provisions of this Act, become or be void, as the`
  line `case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (19202)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Form of business in which banking companies may engage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 4, for "managing agent" (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19202&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to the business`
  line `of banking, a banking company may engage in any one or more of the following forms of business,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the borrowing, raising, or taking up of money; the lending or advancing of money either`
  line `upon or without security; the drawing, making, accepting, discounting, buying, selling, collecting`
  line `and dealing in bills of exchange, hoondees, promissory notes, coupons, drafts, bills of lading,`
  line `railway receipts, warrants, debentures, certificates, scripts and other instruments, and securities`
  line `whether transferable or negotiable or not; the granting and issuing of letters of credit, traveller's`
  line `cheques and circular notes; the buying, selling and dealing in bullion and specie; the buying and`
  line `selling of foreign exchange including foreign bank notes; the acquiring, holding, issuing on`
  line `commission, underwriting and dealing in stock, funds, shares, debentures, debenture stock, bonds,`
  line `obligations, securities and investments of all kinds; the purchasing and selling of bonds, scripts or`
  line `other forms of securities on behalf of constituents or others, the negotiating of loans and advances;`
  line `the receiving of all kinds of bonds, scripts or valuables on deposit or for safe custody or otherwise;`
  line `the providing of safe deposit vaults; the collecting and transmitting of money and securities;`
  line
  line `(b) acting as agents for any Government or local authority or any other person or persons; the`
  line `carrying on of agency business of any description including the clearing and forwarding of goods,`
  line `giving of receipts and discharges and otherwise acting as an attorney on behalf of customers but`
  line `excluding the business of a ^1[managing agent or secretary and treasurer] of a company;`
  line
  line `(c) contracting for public and private loans and negotiating and issuing the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the effecting, insuring, guranteeing, underwriting, participating in managing and carrying`
  line `out of any issue, public or private, of State, municipal or other loans or of shares, stock, debentures`
  line `or debenture stock of any company, corporation or association and the lending of money for the`
  line `purpose of any such issue;`
  line
  line `(e) carrying on and transacting every kind of guarantee and indemnity business;`
  line
  line `(f) managing, selling and realising any property which may come into the possession of the`
  line `company in satisfaction or part satisfaction of any of its claims;`
  line
  line `(g) acquiring and holding and generally dealing with any property or any right, title or interest`
  line `in any such property which may form the security or part of the security for any loans or advances`
  line `or which may be connected with any such security;`
  line
  line `(h) undertaking and executing trusts;`
  line
  line `(i) undertaking the administration of estates as executor, trustee or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(j) establishing and supporting or aiding in the establishment and support of associations,`
  line `institutions, funds, trusts and conveniences calculated to benefit employees or ex-employees of the`
  line `company or the dependents or connections of such persons; granting pensions and allowances and making payments towards insurance; subscribing to or guaranteeing moneys for charitable or`
  line `benevolent objects or for any exhibition or for any public, general or useful object;`
  line
  line `(k) the acquisition, construction, maintenance and alteration of any building or works necessary`
  line `or convenient for the purposes of the company;`
  line
  line `(l) selling, improving, managing, developing, exchanging, leasing, mortgaging, disposing of or`
  line `turning into account or otherwise dealing with all or any part of the property and rights of the`
  line company;
  line
  line `(m) acquiring and undertaking the whole or any part of the business of any person or company,`
  line `when such business is of a nature enumerated or described in this sub-section;`
  line
  line `(n) doing all such other things as are incidental or conducive to the promotion or advancement`
  line `of the business of the company;`
  line
  line `(o) any other form of business which the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify as a form of business in which it is lawful for a banking company to`
  line engage.
  line
  line `(2) No banking company shall engage in any form of business other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (19203)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Use of words "bank", "banker", "banking" or "banking company".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19203&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Use of words "bank", "banker", "banking" or "banking company".--(1) No company`
  line `other than a banking company shall use as part of its name ^2[or in connection with its business] any of`
  line `the words "bank", "banker" or "banking" and no company shall carry on the business of banking in`
  line `India unless it uses as part of its name at least one of such words.`
  line
  line `(2) No firm, individual or group of individuals shall, for the purpose of carrying on any business,`
  line `use as part of its or his name any of the words "bank", "banking" or "banking company".`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) a subsidiary of a banking company formed for one or more of the purposes mentioned in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 19, whose name indicates that it is a subsidiary of that banking company;`
  line
  line `(b) any association of banks formed for the protection of their mutual interests and registered`
  line `under section 25 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1963, s. 7, for section 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (19204)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Prohibition of trading.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19204&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6 or in any contract, no`
  line `banking company shall directly or indirectly deal in the buying or selling or bartering of goods, except`
  line `in connection with the realisation of security given to or held by it, or engage in any trade, or buy, sell`
  line `or barter goods for others otherwise than in connection with bills of exchange received for collection or`
  line `negotiation or with such of its business as is referred to in clause (i) sub-section (1) of section 6:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that this section shall not apply to any such business as is specified in pursuance of`
  line `clause (o) of sub-section (1) of section 6.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "goods" means every kind of moveable property,`
  line `other than actionable claims, stocks, shares, money, bullion and specie, and all instruments referred to`
  line `in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (19205)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Disposal of non-banking assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19205&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6, no banking`
  line `company shall hold any immovable property howsoever acquired, except such as is required for its own`
  line `use, for any period exceeding seven years from the acquisition thereof or from the commencement of`
  line `this Act, whichever is later or any extension of such period as in this section provided, and such`
  line `property shall be disposed of within such period or extended period, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the banking company may, within the period of seven years as aforesaid, deal or trade`
  line `in any such property for the purpose of facilitating the disposal thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Reserve Bank may in any particular case, extend the aforesaid period of`
  line `seven years by such period not exceeding five years where it is satisfied that such extension would be in`
  line `the interest of the depositors of the banking company.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (19206)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition of employment of managing agents and restrictions on certain forms of employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19206&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Prohibition of employment of managing agents and restrictions on certain forms of`
  line `employment.--(1) No banking company--`
  line
  line `(a) shall employ or be managed by a managing agent; or`
  line
  line `(b) shall employ or continue the employment of any person--`
  line
  line `(i) who is, or at any time has been, adjudicated insolvent, or has suspended payment or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or who is, or has been, convicted by a criminal court of an`
  line `offence involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(ii) whose remuneration or part of whose remuneration takes the form of commission or of`
  line `a share in the profits of the company:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-clause shall apply to the payment by a`
  line `banking company of--`
  line
  line `(a) any bonus in pursuance of a settlement or award arrived at or made under any law`
  line `relating to industrial disputes or in accordance with any scheme framed by such banking`
  line `company or in accordance with the usual practice prevailing in banking business;`
  line
  line `(b) any commission to any broker (including guarantee broker), cashier-contractor,`
  line `clearing and forwarding agent, auctioneer or any other person, employed by the banking`
  line `company under a contract otherwise than as a regular member of the staff of the company;`
  line or]
  line
  line `(iii) whose remuneration is, in the opinion of the Reserve Bank, excessive; or`
  line
  line `(c) shall be managed by any person--`
  line
  line `^3[(i) who is a director of any other company not being--`
  line
  line `(a) a subsidiary of the banking company, or`
  line
  line `(b) a company registered under section 25 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956):`
  line
  line `Provided that the prohibition in this sub-clause shall not apply in respect of any such`
  line `director for a temporary period not exceeding three months or such further period not exceeding`
  line `nine months as the Reserve Bank may allow; or]`
  line
  line `(ii) who is engaged in any other business or vocation; or`
  line
  line `(iii) ^4[whose term of office as a person managing the company is] for a period exceeding`
  line `five years at any one time:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that the term of office of any such person may be renewed or extended by further`
  line `periods not exceeding five years on each occasion subject to the condition that such renewal or`
  line `extension shall not be sanctioned earlier than two years from the date on which it is to come into force:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the term of office of such person is for an indefinite period, such term,`
  line `unless it otherwise comes to an end earlier, shall come to an end immediately on the expiry of five years`
  line `from the date of his appointment or on the expiry of three months from the date of commencement of`
  line `section 8 of the Banking Laws (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act, 1963 (55 of 1963), whichever is later:]`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this clause shall apply to a director, other than the managing`
  line `director, of a banking company by reason only of his being such director.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of sub-clause (iii) of clause (b), the expression "remuneration", in`
  line `relation to person employed or continued in employment, shall include salary, fees and perquisites but`
  line `shall not include any allowances or other amounts paid to him for the purpose of reimbursing him in`
  line `respect of the expenses actually incurred by him in the performance of his duties.`
  line
  line `(2) In forming its opinion under sub-clause (iii) of clause (b) sub-section (1), the Reserve Bank may`
  line `have regard among other matters to the following:--`
  line
  line `(i) the financial condition and history of the banking company, its size and area of operation, its`
  line `resources, the volume of its business, and the trend of its earning capacity;`
  line
  line `(ii) the number of its branches or offices;`
  line
  line `(iii) the qualifications, age and experience of the person concerned;`
  line
  line `(iv) the remuneration paid to other persons employed by the banking company or to any person`
  line `occupying a similar position in any other banking company similarly situated; and`
  line
  line `(v) the interests of its depositors.`
  line
  line `^6[^7* * * * *`
  line
  line `(6) Any decision or order of the Reserve Bank made under this section shall be final for all`
  line purposes.]]
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 95 of 1956, s. 2, for section 10 (w.e.f. 14-1-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 6, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-clause (i) (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 55 of 1963, s. 8, for "who has a contract with the company for its management" (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for the first proviso (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 6, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `7. Omitted by Act 55 of 1963, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (19207)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 12
  title `Board of directors to include persons with professional or other experience.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19207&sectionno=10A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Board of directors to include persons with professional or other experience.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, every banking`
  line company,--
  line
  line `(a) in existence on the commencement of section 3 of the Banking Laws (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1968 (58 of 1968), or`
  line
  line `(b) which comes into existence thereafter,`
  line
  line `shall comply with the requirements of this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to a banking company referred to in`
  line `clause (a) for a period of three months from such commencement.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fifty-one per cent. of the total number of members of the Board of directors of a`
  line `banking company shall consist of persons, who--`
  line
  line `(a) shall have special knowledge or practical experience in respect of one or more of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) accountancy,`
  line
  line `(ii) agriculture and rural economy,`
  line
  line `(iii) banking,`
  line
  line `(iv) co-operation,`
  line
  line `(v) economics,`
  line
  line `(vi) finance,`
  line
  line `(vii) law,`
  line
  line `(viii) small-scale industry,`
  line
  line `(ix) any other matter the special knowledge of, and practical experience in, which would, in`
  line `the opinion of the Reserve Bank, be useful to the banking company:`
  line
  line `Provided that out of the aforesaid number of directors, not less than two shall be persons having`
  line `special knowledge or practical experience in respect of agriculture and rural economy, co-operation or`
  line `small-scale industry; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall not--`
  line
  line `(1) have substantial interest in, or be connected with, whether as employee, manager or`
  line `managing agent,--`
  line
  line `(i) any company, not being a company registered under section 25 of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956.), or`
  line
  line `(ii) any firm, which carries on any trade, commerce or industry and which, in either`
  line `case, is not a small-scale industrial concern, or`
  line
  line `(2) be proprietors of any trading, commercial or industrial concern, not being a small-scale`
  line `industrial concern.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), or in any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(i) no director of a banking company, other than its chairman or whole-time director, by`
  line `whatever name called, shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding eight years;`
  line
  line `(ii) a chairman or other whole-time director of a banking company who has been removed from`
  line `office as such chairman, or whole-time director, as the case may be, under the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall also cease to be a director of the banking company and shall also not be eligible to be`
  line `appointed as a director of such banking company, whether by election or co-option or otherwise, for`
  line `a period of four years from the date of his ceasing to be the chairman or whole-time director, as the`
  line `case may be.]`
  line
  line `(3) If, in respect of any banking company, the requirements, as laid down in sub-section (2), are not`
  line `fulfilled at any time, the Board of directors of such banking company shall re-constitute such Board so`
  line `as to ensure that the said requirements are fulfilled.`
  line
  line `(4) If, for the purpose of re-constituting the Board under sub-section (3), it is necessary to retire any`
  line `director or directors, the Board may, by lots drawn in such manner as may be prescribed, decide which`
  line `director or directors shall cease to hold office and such decision shall be binding on every director of`
  line `the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Reserve Bank is of opinion that the composition of the Board of directors of a`
  line `banking company is such that it does not fulfil the requirements of sub-section (2), it may, after giving`
  line `to such banking company a reasonable opportunity of being heard, by an order in writing, direct the`
  line `banking company to so re-constitute its Board of directors as to ensure that the said requirements are`
  line `fulfilled and, if within two months from the date of receipt of that order, the banking company does not`
  line `comply with the directions made by the Reserve Bank, that Bank may, after determining, by lots drawn`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed, the person who ought to be removed from the membership of the`
  line `Board of directors, remove such person from the office of the director of such banking company and`
  line `with a view to complying with the provisions of sub-section (2), appoint a suitable person as a member of the Board of directors in the place of the person so removed whereupon the person so appointed shall`
  line `be deemed to have been duly elected by the banking company as its director.`
  line
  line `(6) Every appointment, removal or reconstitution duly made, and every election duly held, under`
  line `this section shall be final and shall not be called into question in any court.`
  line
  line `(7) Every director elected or, as the case may be, appointed under this section shall hold office until`
  line `the date up to which his predecessor would have held office, if the election had not been held, or, as the`
  line `case may be, the appointment had not been made.`
  line
  line `(8) No act or proceeding of the Board of directors of a banking company shall be invalid by reason`
  line `only of any defect in the composition thereof or on the ground that it is subsequently discovered that`
  line `any of its members did not fulfil the requirements of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 16 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (19208)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 13
  title `Banking company to be managed by whole time chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19208&sectionno=10B&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Banking company to be managed by whole time chairman.--^2[(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any law for the time being in force or in any contract to the contrary, every`
  line `banking company in existence on the commencement of the Banking Regulation (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1994 (20 of 1994), or which comes into existence thereafter shall have one of its directors, who may be`
  line `appointed on a whole-time or a part-time basis as chairman of its Board of directors, and where he is`
  line `appointed on a whole-time basis, as chairman of its Board of directors, he shall be entrusted with the`
  line `management of the whole of the affairs of the banking company:`
  line
  line `Provided that the chairman shall exercise his powers subject to the superintendence, control and`
  line `direction of the Board of directors.`
  line
  line `(1A) Where a chairman is appointed on a part-time basis,--`
  line
  line `(i) such appointment shall be with the previous approval of the Reserve Bank and be subject to`
  line `such conditions as the Reserve Bank may specify while giving such approval;`
  line
  line `(ii) the management of the whole of the affairs of such banking company shall be entrusted to a`
  line `managing director who shall exercise his powers subject to the superintendence, control and`
  line `direction of the Board of directors.]`
  line
  line `(2) ^3[Every chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed on a whole-time basis and every`
  line `managing director] of a banking company shall be in the whole time employment of such company and`
  line `shall hold office for such period, not exceeding five years, as the Board of directors may fix, but shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this section, be eligible for re-election or re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as prohibiting a chairman from being a`
  line `director of a subsidiary of the banking company or a director of a company registered under section 25`
  line `of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) Every person holding office on the commencement of section 3 of the Banking Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1968 (58 of 1968), as managing director of a banking company shall--`
  line
  line `(a) if there is a chairman of its Board of directors, vacate office on such commencement, or`
  line
  line `(b) if there is no chairman of its Board of directors, vacate office on the date on which the`
  line `chairman of its Board of directors is elected or appointed in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(4)`
  line `^4[Every chairman who is appointed on a whole-time basis and every managing director of a`
  line `banking company appointed under sub-section (1A)] shall be a person who has special knowledge and`
  line `practical experience of--`
  line
  line `(a) the working of a banking company, or of the State Bank of India or any subsidiary bank or a`
  line `financial institution, or`
  line
  line `(b) financial, economic or business administration:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall be disqualified for being a ^5[chairman who is appointed on a`
  line `whole-time basis or a managing director] if he--`
  line
  line `(a) is a director of any company other than a company referred to in the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (2), or`
  line
  line `(b) is a partner of any firm which carries on any trade, business or industry, or`
  line
  line `(c) has substantial interest in any other company or firm, or`
  line
  line `(d) is a director, manager, managing agent, partner or proprietor of any trading, commercial or`
  line `industrial concern, or`
  line
  line `(e) is engaged in any other business or vocation.`
  line
  line `(5) ^6[A chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director]`
  line `of a banking company may, by writing, under his hand addressed to the company, resign his office,`
  line ^7***
  line
  line `^8[(5A) ^6[A chairman of the Board of directors appoint on a whole-time basis or a managing director]`
  line `whose term of office has come to an end, either by reason of his resignation or by reason of expiry of`
  line `the period of his office, shall, subject to the approval of the Reserve Bank, continue in office until his`
  line `successor assumes office.]`
  line
  line `(6) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 36AA, where the Reserve Bank is of opinion that`
  line `any person who is, or has been elected to be, the ^9[chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed`
  line `on a whole-time basis or the managing director] of a banking company is not a fit and proper person to`
  line `hold such office, it may, after giving to such person and to the banking company a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, require the banking company to elect or appoint any`
  line `other person as the ^10[chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed on a whole-time basis or the`
  line `managing director] and if, within a period of two months from the date of receipt of such order, the`
  line `banking company fails to elect or appoint a suitable person as the ^10[chairman of the Board of directors`
  line `who is appointed on a whole-time basis or the managing director] the Reserve Bank may, by order,`
  line `remove the first-mentioned person from the office of the ^9[chairman of the Board of directors who is`
  line `appointed on a whole-time basis or the managing director] of the banking company and appoint a`
  line `suitable person in his place whereupon the person so appointed shall be deemed to have been duly`
  line `elected or appointed, as the case may be, as the ^9[chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed`
  line `on a whole-time basis or the managing director] of such banking company and any persons elected or`
  line `^11[appointed as chairman on a whole-time basis or managing director] under this sub-section shall hold`
  line `office for the residue of the period of office of the person is whose place he has been so elected or`
  line appointed.
  line
  line `(7) The banking company and any person against whom an order of removal is made under`
  line `sub-section (6) may, within thirty days from the date of communication to it or to him of the order,`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Central Government and the decision of the Central Government thereon, and`
  line `subject thereto, the order made by the Reserve Bank under sub-section (6), shall be final and shall not`
  line `be called into question in any court.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Reserve Bank may, if in its opinion it is`
  line `necessary in the public interest so to do, permit ^12[the chairman of the Board of directors who is`
  line `appointed on a whole-time basis or the managing director] to undertake such part-time honorary work`
  line `as is not likely to interfere with his duties as ^13[such chairman or managing director].`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where a person ^14`
  line `[appointed on a`
  line `whole-time basis, as chairman of the Board of directors or managing director] dies or resigns or is by`
  line `infirmity or otherwise rendered incapable of carrying out his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise in`
  line `circumstances not involving the vacation of his office, the banking company may, with the approval of`
  line `the Reserve Bank, make suitable arrangements for carrying out the ^15[duties of chairman or managing`
  line `director] for a total period not exceeding four months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-2-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 2, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Every chairman of the Board of directors" (w.e.f. 31-1-1984).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "Every chairman of the Board of directors of a banking company" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 2, for "chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "A chairman of the Board of directors" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `7. The words "but shall continue in office until his successor assumes office" omitted by Act 1 of 1984, s. 17`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 2, for "chairman of the Board of directors" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "chairman of its Board of directors" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "appointed as chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 2, for "the chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "such chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "appointed as chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "duties as chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_bb:
  sectionId (19209)
  sectionNo 10BB
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to appoint chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director of a banking company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_bb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_bb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19209&sectionno=10BB&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_bb_content:
  string
  line `^1[10BB. Power of Reserve Bank to appoint ^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on`
  line `on a whole-time basis or a managing director] of a banking company.--(1) Where the office of the`
  line `^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director] of a`
  line `banking company is vacant, the Reserve Bank may, if it is of opinion that the continuation of such`
  line `vacancy is likely to adversely affect the interests of the banking company, appoint a person, eligible`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 10B to be so appointed, to be the ^2[chairman of the Board of directors`
  line `appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director] of the banking company and where the person`
  line `so appointed is not a director of such banking company, he shall, so long as he holds the office of the`
  line `^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director], be`
  line `deemed to be a director of the banking company.`
  line
  line `(2) The ^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing`
  line `director] so appointed by the Reserve Bank shall be in the whole-time employment of the banking`
  line `company and shall hold office for such period not exceeding three years, as the Reserve Bank may`
  line `specify, but shall, subject to other provisions of this Act, be a eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing`
  line `director] so appointed by the Reserve Bank shall draw from the banking company such pay and`
  line `allowances as the Reserve Bank may determine and may be removed from office only by the Reserve`
  line Bank.
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in this section, the provisions of section 10B shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to the ^2[chairman of the Board of directors appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing`
  line `director] appointed by the Reserve Bank under sub-section (1) as they apply to a ^2[chairman of the`
  line `Board of directors appointed on a whole- time basis or a managing director] appointed by the banking`
  line company]
obj_root_law_sections_10_bb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 18 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 3, for "chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_c:
  sectionId (19210)
  sectionNo 10C
  orderNo 15
  title `Chairman and certain directors not to be required to hold qualification shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19210&sectionno=10C&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[10C. Chairman and certain directors not to be required to hold qualification shares.--^2[A`
  line `chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed on a whole-time basis or a managing director] of a`
  line `banking company (by whomsoever appointed) and a director of a banking company (appointed by the`
  line `Reserve Bank under section 10A) shall not be required to hold qualification shares in the banking`
  line company.]
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 19, for section 10C (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 4, for "A chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
