  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19211&sectionno=10D&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_10_d_content:
  string
  line `Any appointment or removal of a ^1[director, chairman of the Board of directors who is appointed`
  line `on a whole-time basis or managing director] in pursuance of section 10A or section 10B ^2[or section`
  line `10BB] shall have effect and any such person shall not be entitled to claim any compensation for the loss`
  line `or termination of office, notwithstanding anything contained in any law or in any contract,`
  line `memorandum or articles of association.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 5, for "director or chairman" (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 20 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (19212)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 17
  title `Requirement as to minimum paid-up capital and reserves.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19212&sectionno=11&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in ^1[section 149 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)], no banking company in existence`
  line `on the commencement of this Act, shall, after the expiry of three years from such commencement or of`
  line `such further period not exceeding one year as the Reserve Bank, having regard to the interests of the`
  line `depositors of the company, may think fit in any particular case to allow, carry on business ^2[in India],`
  line `and no other banking company shall after the commencement of this Act, commence or carry on`
  line `business ^2[in India], ^3[unless it complies with such of the requirements of this section as are applicable`
  line `to it].`
  line
  line `^4[(2) In the case of a banking company incorporated outside India--`
  line
  line `(a) the aggregate value of its paid-up capital and reserves shall not be less than fifteen lakhs of`
  line `rupees and if it has a place or places of business in the city of Bombay or Calcutta or both, twenty`
  line `lakhs of rupees; and`
  line
  line `(b) ^5[the banking company shall deposit and keep deposited with the Reserve Bank either in`
  line `cash or in the form of unencumbered approved securities, or partly in cash and partly in the form of`
  line `such securities--`
  line
  line `(i) an amount which shall not be less than the minimum required by clause (a); and`
  line
  line `(ii) as soon as may be after the expiration of each ^6*** year, an amount calculated at twenty`
  line `twenty per cent. of its profit for that year in respect of all business transacted through its`
  line `branches in India, as disclosed in the profit and loss account prepared with reference to that`
  line `year under section 29:]`
  line
  line `Provided that any such banking company may at any time replace--`
  line
  line `(i) any securities so deposited by cash or by any other unencumbered approved securities, or`
  line `partly by cash and partly by other such securities, so however, that the total amount deposited is not`
  line affected;
  line
  line `(ii) any cash so deposited by unencumbered approved securities of an equal value.]`
  line
  line `^7[(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Central Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of the Reserve Bank, and having regard to the adequacy of the amounts already`
  line `deposited and kept deposited by a banking company under sub-section (2), in relation to its deposit`
  line `liabilities in India, declare by order in writing that the provisions of sub-clause (ii) of clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) shall not apply to such banking company for such period as may be specified in the`
  line order.]
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any banking company to which the provisions of sub-section (2) do not apply, the`
  line `aggregate value of its paid-up capital and reserves shall not be less than--`
  line
  line `(i) if it has places of business in more than one State, five lakhs of rupees, and if any such place`
  line `or places of business is or are situated in the city of Bombay or Calcutta or both, ten lakhs of`
  line rupees;
  line
  line `(ii) if it has all its places of business in one State none of which is situated in the city of`
  line `Bombay or Calcutta, one lakh of rupees in respect of its principal place of business, plus ten`
  line `thousand rupees in respect of each of its other places of business situated in the same district in`
  line `which it has its principal place of business, plus twenty-five thousand rupees in respect of each`
  line `place of business situated elsewhere in the State otherwise than in the same district:`
  line
  line `Provided that no banking company to which this clause applies shall be required to have paidup capital and reserves exceeding an aggregated value of five lakhs of rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no banking company to which this clause applies and which has only one`
  line `place of business shall be required to have paid-up capital and reserves exceeding an aggregate`
  line `value of fifty thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided further that in the case of every banking company to which this clause applies and`
  line `which commences banking business for the first time after the commencement of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Amendment) Act, 1962 (36 of 1962), the value of its paid-up capital shall not be less`
  line `than five lakhs of rupees;]`
  line
  line `(iii) if it has all its places of business in one State, one or more of which is or are situated in the`
  line `city of Bombay or Calcutta, five lakhs of rupees, plus twenty-five thousand rupees in respect of`
  line `each place of business situated outside the city of Bombay or Calcutta, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no banking company to which this clause applies shall be required to have`
  line `paid-up capital and reserves exceeding an aggregate value of ten lakhs of rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a place of business situated ^9[in a State] other`
  line `than that in which the principal place of business of the banking company is situated shall, if it is not`
  line `more than twenty-five miles distant from such principal place of business, be deemed to be situated`
  line `within the same State as such principal place of business.`
  line
  line `(4) Any amount deposited and kept deposited with the Reserve Bank under ^10*** sub-section (2) by`
  line `any banking company incorporated ^11[outside India] shall, in the event of the company ceasing for any`
  line `reason to carry on banking business ^12[in India], be an asset of the company on which the claims of all`
  line `the creditors of the company ^12[in India] shall be a first charge.`
  line
  line `^13[(5) For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "place of business" means any office, sub-office, sub- pay office and any place of business`
  line `at which deposits are received, cheques cashed or moneys lent;`
  line
  line `(b) "value" means the real or exchangeable value, and not the nominal value which may be`
  line `shown in the books of the banking company concerned.]`
  line
  line `(6) If any dispute arises in computing the aggregate value of the paid-up capital and reserves of any`
  line `banking company, a determination thereof by the Reserve Bank shall be final for the purposes of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 95 of 1956, s. 14 and the Schedule, for "section 103 of the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)" (w.e.f. 14-1-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1950, s. 3, for "in any State" (w.e.f. 18-3-1950).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 7, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10- 1959).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `6. The word"calendar" omitted by Act 66 of 1988, s. 7 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 36 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-9-1962).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 36 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-9-1962).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and Sch., for "in India" (w.e.f. 1- 11-1956).`
  line
  line `10. The words "the proviso to" omitted by Act 33 of 1959, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 20 of 1950, s. 3, for "elsewhere than in a State" (w.e.f. 18-3-1950).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "in the States"(w.e.f. 18-3-1950).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 7, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 1-10- 1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (19213)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 18
  title `Regulation of paid-up capital, subscribed capital and authorised capital and voting rights of shareholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779&sectionId=19213&sectionno=12&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00002_194910_1517807317779
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Regulation of paid-up capital, subscribed capital and authorised capital and voting`
  line `rights of shareholders.-- (1) No banking company shall carry on business in India, unless it satisfies`
  line `the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) that the subscribed capital of the company is not less than one-half of the authorised capital,`
  line `and the paid- up capital is not less than one-half of the subscribed capital and that, if the capital is`
  line `increased, it complies with the conditions prescribed in this clause within such period not exceeding`
  line `two years as the Reserve Bank may allow;`
  line
  line `^2[(ii) that, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the`
  line `capital of such banking company consists of--`
  line
  line `(a) equity shares only; or`
  line
  line `(b) equity shares and preferences shares:`
  line
  line `Provided that the issue of preference share shall be in accordance with the guidelines`
  line `framed by the Reserve Bank specifying the class of preference shares, the extent of issue of`
  line `each class of such preference shares (whether perpetual or irredeemable or redeemable), and the`
  line `terms and conditions subject to which each class of preference shares may be issued:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no holder of the preference share, issued by the company, shall be`
  line `entitled to exercise the voting right specified in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 87 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) No person holding shares in a banking company shall, in respect of any shares held by him,`
  line `exercise voting rights ^4[on poll] ^5[in excess of ^6[ten per cent]] of the total voting rights of all the shareshare-holders of the banking company:`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that the Reserve Bank may increase, in a phased manner, such ceiling on voting rights`
  line `from ten per cent. to twenty-six per cent.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force or in any contract or`
  line `instrument no suit or other proceeding shall be maintained against any person registered as the holder of`
  line `a share in a banking company on the ground that the title to the said share vests in a person other than`
  line `the registered holder:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall bar a suit or other proceeding--`
  line
  line `(a) by a transferee of the share on the ground that he has obtained from the registered holder a`
  line `transfer of the share in accordance with any law relating to such transfer; or`
  line
  line `(b) on behalf of a minor or a lunatic on the ground that the registered holder holds the share on`
  line `behalf of the minor or lunatic.`
  line
  line `(4) Every chairman, managing director or chief executive officer by whatever name called of a`
  line `banking company shall furnish to the Reserve Bank through that banking company returns containing`
  line `full particulars of the extent and value of his holding of shares, whether directly or indirectly, in the`
  line `banking company and of any change in the extent of such holding or any variation in the rights`
  line `attaching thereto and such other information relating to those shares as the Reserve Bank may, by order,`
  line `require and in such form and at such time as may be specified in the order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 95 of 1956, s. 3, for section 12 (w.e.f. 14- 1-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 3, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 18-1-2013).`
  line
  line `3. The proviso omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 18-1-2013).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 1959, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-10-1959).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 55 of 1963, s. 9, for in excess of five per cent. (w.e.f. 1-2-1964).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 20 of 1994, s. 6, for one per cen. (w.e.f. 31-1-1994).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 3 (w.e.f. 18-1-2013).`
